# CSS Layout

Examine this image showing CSS layout concepts:

![CSS Box Model](https://www.washington.edu/accesscomputing/webd2/student/unit3/images/boxmodel.gif)

Given the following CSS:

```css
.box {
  width: 300px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 5px solid black;
  margin: 10px;
  box-sizing: content-box;
}
```

Calculate the total width of this element as rendered in the browser, explaining each component. Then explain how this would change if you used `box-sizing: border-box` instead.

# JavaScript Scope

```javascript
let count = 10;
const message = 'Hello';
var flag = true;

function updateCount() {
  let count = 20;
  console.log(count); // Line A

  if (flag) {
    var localFlag = false;
    let localMessage = 'Hi';
    console.log(message); // Line B
  }

  console.log(localFlag); // Line C
  console.log(localMessage); // Line D
}

updateCount();
console.log(count); // Line E
```

What values will be logged at lines A, B, C, D, and E? Explain the scope differences between `let`, `const`, and `var`, and identify any errors in this code.

# DOM Manipulation

Examine this JavaScript code:

```javascript
document.getElementById('submit-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
  const name = document.getElementById('name-input').value;
  const email = document.getElementById('email-input').value;

  if (name && email) {
    const listItem = document.createElement('li');
    listItem.textContent = `${name}: ${email}`;
    document.getElementById('user-list').appendChild(listItem);

    document.getElementById('name-input').value = '';
    document.getElementById('email-input').value = '';
  }
});
```

1. What does this code do?
2. Identify two potential issues with this implementation
3. Rewrite this using modern JavaScript practices
4. How would you improve the user experience with this form?
